atch):\n        # build a store with two first_seen groups where the 2nd group\n        # would straddle the --limit boundary if truncated mid-group\n        ...  # requires a Store fixture seeded with two diff() calls\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `fetchers.py` — largest surface, largest gap, 0% covered\n\nThis file explicitly documents itself as designed for testability (\"HTTP client is injectable... unit-testable against mocked transports\"), which makes the complete absence of tests here the biggest gap in the repo.\n\n**A. Pure parsers — no I/O, trivial to test, highest value per line:**\n\nEvery `parse_*` function should have at minimum: (1) a normal-payload case, (2) a missing/None-field case (most access via `.get()` defensively — verify the defensiveness actually holds), (3) an empty list case.\n\nSpecific edge cases already flagged by comments in the code but never verified:\n- `parse_lever` / `_lever_salary`: `lo`/`hi` present with int formatting (`\"1,000\"`) vs `salaryDescriptionPlain` fallback vs neither → `\"\"`\n- `parse_ashby` / `parse_ashby_page`: `isListed: False` postings excluded\n- `parse_google` / `_extract_ds1`: malformed/absent `ds:1` blob → `[]`, not a crash\n- `parse_google` / `_ds1_posted_at`: index-out-of-range on short arrays (defensive `len(job) > idx`)\n- `parse_deshaw`: duplicate `data-job-id` cards deduped via `seen`\n- `parse_twosigma`: same role rendering 3× (layout variants) deduped\n- `parse_apple` / `_apple_posted_at`: nanosecond timestamp truncated to microseconds — malformed timestamp → `\"\"` not a raise\n- `parse_apple`: multi-location job produces deduped, comma-joined location string (`dict.fromkeys`)\n- `_amazon_posted_at`: valid `\"June 26, 2026\"` → ISO; malformed string → `\"\"` (catches `ValueError`/`KeyError`)\n- `parse_bytedance` / `_bd_location`: recursive `parent` chain walk, missing `city_info` → `\"\"`\n- `_balanced_json`: nested braces inside a string value (e.g. `{\"x\": \"a{b}c\"}`) don't confuse depth counting; unbalanced input → `None`\n- `_apple_hydration`: escaped quotes inside the `JSON.parse(\"...\")` string handled correctly\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_google, parse_deshaw,\n                       _amazon_posted_at, parse_amazon, _balanced_json,\n                       _bd_location, parse_bytedance)\n\nclass TestGreenhouse:\n    def test_normal_payload(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}], \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"NYC\" and jobs[0].department == \"Eng\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_location_and_departments(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_min_max_formats_with_commas(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_plain(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAshbyListedFilter:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_excluded(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                          {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].title == \"Visible\"\n\n\nclass TestBalancedJson:\n    def test_extracts_balanced_object(self):\n        text = 'prefix{\"a\": {\"b\": 1}}suffix'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, text.index(\"{\")) == '{\"a\": {\"b\": 1}}'\n\n    def test_braces_inside_string_dont_confuse_depth(self):\n        text = '{\"a\": \"a{b}c\"}'\n        assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n    def test_unbalanced_returns_none(self):\n        assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n\n\nclass TestGoogleDs1:\n    def test_extract_ds1_missing_blob_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>nothing here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json], sideChannel\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_short_array_no_crash(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([\"id\", \"title\"]) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Frobtember 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestBdLocation:\n    def test_walks_parent_chain(self):\n        city = {\"en_name\": \"SF\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"CA\",\n                 \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\", \"parent\": None}}}\n        assert _bd_location(city) == \"SF, CA, USA\"\n\n    def test_missing_city_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n```\n\n**B. `_request` retry/backoff — the resilience contract, untested:**\n\n| Gap |\n|---|\n| 429/500/502/503/504 → retries up to `retries` times |\n| Non-retryable 4xx (e.g. 400/404) → raises immediately, no retry |\n| Success on a later attempt returns the response |\n| Exhausted retries → `RuntimeError` wrapping the last exception |\n| Backoff sleep is bounded (`min(..., 30)`) — never actually sleeps 30s in a test (patch `asyncio.sleep`) |\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_request.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"asyncio.sleep\", lambda *_: None)  # skip real backoff\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=3)\n    assert r.status_code == 200\n    assert route.call_count == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_non_retryable_4xx_raises_immediately():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(Exception):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=3)\n    assert route.call_count == 1  # no retry attempted\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"asyncio.sleep\", lambda *_: None)\n    respx.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(503))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=2)\n```\n\n**C. Paginated `fetch_*` loop logic — the trickiest untested behavior in the file:**\n\nEvery one of `fetch_ashby`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_bytedance`, `fetch_phenom`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_meta`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon` implements its own \"stop when a page returns nothing *new*\" loop with a `seen` set and `max_pages` cap. This pattern is copy-pasted 13 times and **none of it is tested**:\n\n| Gap |\n|---|\n| Stops pagination when a page returns an empty/no-new batch |\n| Respects `max_pages` cap even if the server would return more |\n| Dedupes across pages (`seen` set) — same id appearing on two pages doesn't duplicate |\n| `fetch_ashby`: posting-api 404 falls back to hosted-page `__appData` scrape; non-404 non-200 raises |\n| `fetch_workday`: safety cap at `offset > 5000` |\n| `fetch_meta`: `doc_id` rotation surfaces as a clear `RuntimeError` (the exact failure mode the module docstring warns about) |\n| `fetch_meta`: `\"for (;;);\"` JSONP prefix stripped before parsing |\n| `fetch_source`: unknown `ats` key raises `ValueError` listing known ATSes |\n| `fetch_all`: one source's exception doesn't abort others, returns `[]` for that source, logs to stdout |\n| `fetch_all`: results from all sources are flattened into one list |\n| `fetch_all`: `concurrency` actually bounds simultaneous in-flight requests (semaphore) |\n| `fetch_all`: client lifecycle — owns and closes a client it created; does **not** close a client passed in (`owns_client` flag) |\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_optiver_stops_on_empty_page():\n    respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/a\", \"title\": \"A\"}]}),\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": []}),\n    ])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 40})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_optiver_respects_max_pages_cap():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://www.optiver.com/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n            \"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/x\", \"title\": \"X\"}]}))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 2})\n    assert route.call_count == 2  # capped, even though server \"would\" keep returning items\n\n\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"nonexistent\"})\n\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    @respx.mock\n    async def test_one_source_failure_does_not_abort_others(self, capsys):\n        respx.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/good/jobs\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []}))\n        sources = [\n            {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"},\n            {\"ats\": \"unknown-ats-key\", \"company\": \"bad\"},\n        ]\n        # patch fetch_source dispatch or just let the ValueError propagate through `one()`\n        jobs = await fetch_all(sources, concurrency=2)\n        assert jobs == []  # good source had no jobs, bad source failed silently\n        assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_does_not_close_externally_provided_client(self):\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n        await fetch_all([], client=client)\n        assert not client.is_closed\n        await client.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Integration test gaps (no fetch/store/notify mocking boundary tested together)\n\nNone of these currently exist:\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline run** with a fake in-memory `Store`, stub fetchers, and a captured `dispatch` call — verifying `run()` wires `fetch_all → filter_jobs → Store.diff → dispatch` correctly and returns the right summary dict.\n2. **Two consecutive pipeline runs** against the same DB: run 1 sees jobs as new, run 2 (same jobs, no changes) sees zero new/changed, run 3 (one job's title changed) sees it in `changed` only.\n3. **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` cycle** against a real (tmp) `Store`: first run uses the 7-day default window; after `db-mark <watermark>`, a second `db-new` only returns rows after that watermark — proves the \"never advance marker in db-new\" contract.\n4. **CLI smoke test**: `python cli.py --dry-run -c sources.yaml` against a stubbed network, asserting exit code 0 and no DB mutation (currently would hit real APIs — needs `respx` at the process boundary or refactoring `cli.py`/`pipeline.py` to accept an injectable client, which `fetch_all` already half-supports via its `client` param).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Module | Lines | Functions/classes | Tests | Coverage |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| models.py | 76 | 5 | 0 | 0% |\n| filters.py | 54 | 3 | 0 | 0% |\n| store.py | 137 | 1 class, 10 methods | 0 | 0% |\n| notify.py | 109 | 7 | 0 | 0% |\n| pipeline.py | 52 | 3 | 0 | 0% |\n| cli.py | 18 | 1 | 0 | 0% |\n| agent.py | 341 | 12 | 0 | 0% |\n| fetchers.py | 1146 | ~45 (parsers + fetchers + helpers) | 0 | 0% |\n| **Total** | **1932** | **~90** | **0** | **0%** |\n\n**Recommended sequencing** given zero existing infra: `models.py` and `filters.py` first (pure, no mocking needed, ~30 min), then `store.py` (SQLite, tmp_path fixture), then `fetchers.py` parsers (pure functions, the biggest win), then `_request`/pagination with `respx`, then `notify.py`/`pipeline.py`/`agent.py`, then integration tests last.\n",
